Get a political level's raw supplemental date-specific FOKUS questionnaire data

Source: R/fokus.gen.R
q_suppl_lvl.Rd

Returns a structured list of the raw supplemental date-specific FOKUS questionnaire data for the specified ballot date and political level.

q_suppl_lvl(ballot_date = ballot_dates, lvl = c("cantonal", "federal"))

Arguments

ballot_date

A valid FOKUS-covered cantonal ballot date. One of

  • "2018-09-23"

  • "2018-11-25"

  • "2019-10-20"

  • "2020-09-27"

  • "2020-10-18"
lvl

The political level. One of

  • "cantonal"

  • "federal"

Value

A strict list.

See also

Raw questionnaire data q qx_suppl

Other raw questionnaire data functions q_suppl_election(), q_suppl_lvl_canton(), q_suppl_proposal(), q_suppl_skill_questions(), q_suppl_skill_question(), q_suppl()

Examples

fokus::q_suppl_lvl(ballot_date = "2018-09-23",
                   lvl = "cantonal") |>
  names()

#> [1] "aargau"
